data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['tentətiv]
*tính từ
 ■ướm, thử
 ■ngập ngừng, thăm dò
 ⁃make a tentative suggestion
 đưa ra một đề nghị thăm dò
 ■không dứt khoát, không quả quyết

Anh - Anh
tentative
■ adjective not certain or fixed; provisional.
⁃ hesitant.
Derivatives
tentativelyadverb
tentativenessnoun
Origin
C16: from med. L. tentativus, from tentare, var. of temptare 'handle, try'.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
tentative
▸ adjective
1tentative arrangements | a tentative conclusion: PROVISIONAL, unconfirmed, pencilled in, preliminary, to be confirmed, TBC, subject to confirmation; speculative, conjectural, untried, unproven, exploratory, experimental, trial, test, pilot.
2he took a few tentative steps: HESITANT, uncertain, cautious, timid, hesitating, faltering, shaky, unsteady, halting; wavering, unsure.
Opposites
definite, confident.

sentences.en: However, in early 2004, Boeing announced tentative plans for the 747 Advanced that were eventually adopted.
